  "prompt": "How do I know viewers of my Facebook profile?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, **Facebook does not provide a feature that allows users to see who has viewed their personal profile**. This means there's no official way to track or identify individuals who visit your Facebook profile.\n\n### Why Can't You See Who Viewed Your Profile?\n\nFacebook prioritizes user privacy and does not offer tools to track profile visitors. Unlike some other social media platforms (like LinkedIn, which allows premium users to see who viewed their profiles), Facebook has chosen not to implement this feature to protect user privacy and prevent potential misuse.\n\n### Beware of Third-Party Apps and Services\n\nYou might come across third-party apps, browser extensions, or websites claiming they can show you who has viewed your Facebook profile. **Be cautious with these claims**, as they are often:\n\n1. **Scams**: Many are designed to collect your personal information, spread malware, or engage in fraudulent activities.\n2. **Privacy Risks**: Granting access to these services can compromise your Facebook account and personal data.\n3. **Non-Functional**: Facebook's API does not support sharing profile view data, so these services are unlikely to provide accurate or any information.\n\n**It's best to avoid using such services** to protect your account and personal information.\n\n### What Information Can You Access?\n\nWhile you can't see who viewed your profile, Facebook does provide some insights into engagement with your content:\n\n- **Stories**: If you post Facebook Stories, you can see a list of users who viewed each story during its 24-hour lifespan.\n- **Posts and Interactions**: You can see who has liked, commented on, or shared your posts, giving you an idea of who is engaging with your content.\n\n### Tips to Manage Your Privacy on Facebook\n\nIf you're concerned about who can see your profile and information, consider adjusting your privacy settings:\n\n1. **Navigate to Settings & Privacy**:\n   - Click on the downward arrow (desktop) or the three horizontal lines (mobile) in the top-right corner of Facebook.\n   - Select \"Settings & Privacy\" > \"Settings.\"\n\n2. **Adjust Privacy Settings**:\n   - **Profile Visibility**: Control who can see your posts, friend list, and personal information.\n   - **Activity Status**: Decide whether others can see when you're active on Facebook.\n   - **Blocking**: Block specific users from viewing your profile or interacting with you.\n\n3. **Review Active Sessions**:\n   - Under \"Security and Login,\" you can see the devices where your account is logged in and log out of any unfamiliar sessions.\n\n### Conclusion\n\nWhile it's natural to be curious about who visits your Facebook profile, the platform's privacy policies do not support this feature. Focus on creating engaging content and managing your privacy settings to ensure a safe and enjoyable experience on Facebook. Always be cautious of third-party services that claim to offer profile view information, as they often pose security risks.\n\nIf you have any further questions or need assistance with Facebook settings, feel free to ask!",
